                    <p><b>True facts about misconception on blood donation:</b>
                      <ol>
                      <li>You won't feel drained or tired if your continue to drink fluids and have a good meal.</li>
                      <li>You can resume your normal activities after donating blood, though you are asked to refrain from excercise or heavy weight lifting.</li>
                      <li>Donating blood will not leave you low of blood, in fact you will still have surplus blood after donation.</li>
                      <li>You will not faint or feel uncomfortable after donation.</li>
                      <li>You will not get AIDS if you donate blood.</li>
                    </ol></p>
